values: I sit in my bunker in the battlements of my building.  A pidgeon on a parapet, cigarette pressed between my lips like hugging someone you've missed.  However, I have hurt, holed up inbetween the hurtles, I am passed over, unleavened bread.  I do not rise but remain ridden with riddles.  Queries into qualitative facts I cannot extract from the air no matter how hard I hyperventilate.  I am a savant spewing smoke and smarmy, sicophantic obsession,  "I can change, calibrate, reconvene, become boisterous, buoyant once more."  I suppose I have hope, but that too may just be a musing.
